<TITLE> Narayanganj residents demand more gas </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, Mar 29 (bdnews24.com)Thousands of local people from Fatulla surrounded the Titas Gas zonal office on Monday demanding increased gas supply. The agitating people, from Isdair, Masdair, Gabtoli, West Masdair, North Masdair and Alaminbagh, also staged demonstrations in front of the office at Chashara Balur Math area, threatening tougher action if an immediate solution is not found. The demonstrators said the authority has not taken any effective step despite several complaints. The programme was suspended after the managing director of the Fatulla zonal office Sheikh Abu Raihan assured the protestors that he would take immediate steps to improve the situation.. bdnews24.com correspondent said that the residents and the factories on the outskirts of the capital have been facing a severe gas crisis causing real suffering. The poor supply of gas to the factories, most of which are knitwear manufacturers, also result in a decrease in production. The deputy managing director of Titas's Narayanganj office, Amir Hossain told bdnews24.com that, "We're only receiving about half the gas that we need. "Against a daily demand of 1.44 lakh cubic feet, we're getting only 75 thousand cubic feet," he said. But the situation will improve after the installation of a regulator station, he added. bdnews24
